<blockquote>
    <p>Free writing is a prewriting technique in which a person writes continuously for a set period of time without regard to spelling, grammar, or topic.</p>
    <p>Unlike brainstorming where ideas are simply listed, in freewriting one writes sentences to form a paragraph about whatever comes to mind.</p>
